fields.label: Select Your Timezone
fields.description:
Required to create tasks correctly in Habitica, as well as handling the cutoffs for daily tasks, etc. You should make sure that all 3rd party integrations (Fitbit, Habitica, etc) are set to use the same timezone for best results. 

These are often named using the capital of a country if in a single timezone, or the largest city in the timezone, although a few use country names.

1.title: Fitbit Auth

fields.label: Show If Already Joined
fields.content: It looks like you have already linked your Fitbit account. You only need to link your Fitbit account again if you are having connectivity issues, want to increase granted permissions, or have been otherwise notified.

fields.label: Get FitBit Token
fields.content:
Authenticate with FitBit

At a minimum, you should allow the Activities scope. Weight is used for goals, Nutrition for daily calorie counts.

fields.label: Fitbit Access Code
fields.description: Filled Automatically by Clicking Button above. This is only valid for 10 minutes, so if it has been longer than 10 minutes, click the button to regenerate before submitting. This code is exchanged for an auto-renewing access token.

2.title: Habitica Auth

fields.label: Already Active
fields.content: It looks like you already have an active Habitica link. Unless you need to update your user id or API token, you shouldn't have to submit this form again.

fields.label: Instructions
fields.content: In order to find your ID and API Token, you can visit this link while logged in: https://habitica.com/user/settings/api

2.requireLoginMessage: You must be logged in to use this feature.

confirmations.name: Default Confirmation
confirmations.message: Your account should now be linked with Habitica! If you ever need to change your API secret or User ID, you can always return to this page to authenticate again.

fields.label: Name of Habitica Task to Create
fields.description: Give your task a descriptive name so you'll recognize it! A good rule of thumb is to name it after your completion benchmark: "Lose 10 lbs", "10k steps per day", etc.

fields.label: Task Difficulty
fields.description: Self-rate your task difficulty. The higher the difficulty, the greater the Habitica rewards.

fields.label: Task Type
fields.description: For daily steps, calories in, calories out, "Daily" is the suggested value. For a weight loss or gain goal, "To-Do" is suggested (you can even come back and set up multiple "to-do's" for different levels if you want to mark off as progress is made. If you choose Habit, you may not choose Fitbit as your integration type (not compatible with the type of data).

fields.label: Type of Daily
fields.description: Choose how often your task should be available to complete. You can either pick particular days of the week (Weekly), or on a rotating schedule every X days, like run a mile every 3rd day (Daily)

fields.label: Assign Task To:
fields.description: Which days should this task be required on?

fields.label: Habit Type
fields.description: Choose positive if it's a habit you want more of, negative it's a habit you want less of. Choose both if you want the ability to mark both good and bad days, for gain / loss.

fields.label: Integration Type
fields.description:
Choosing "None" creates a task in Habitica that does not have any auto-completion handling. You can still mark it complete manually.

In order to use any of the other options, you must have already linked the appropriate API under the "Configure Integrations" link.

fields.label: No Habits with Fitbit
fields.content: Fitbit Does not support the Habit type of task currently. (since all stats are daily / lifetimes stats). If you wish to create a stand-alone habit task, please select Integration Type: None above. Otherwise, you may select Daily or Todo to integrate with Fitbit.
